---
description: Safe commit workflow with sensitive-data detection
globs:
alwaysApply: false
---

Follow the commit runbook at `.ai/skills/commit.md` whenever the user asks to commit.

Key rules:
- Scan diff for secrets/credentials before staging anything — abort if found
- Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `chore:`
- Always include a body explaining *why* the change was made
- Stage by explicit file name — never `git add .` or `git add -A`
- No AI co-author or attribution lines in the commit message
